<br>
The Humans would take over the majority of Antonica.  The Ogres and Trolls would get pushed back to their swamps and left to fight it out between them with the Ogres eventually winning that fight.  The Barbarians and would invade Surefall Glade, Jagged Pine, and Black Burrow.  They would blow the entrances and be left in peace by their distant relatives the Humans.<br>
<br>
The battle for Faydwer would be great!  The gnomes would come out of their hole and start putting the smackdown on everyone.  The Wood Elves would be annihilated quickly when one of the gnomes nukes catches GF on fire and burns Kelethin to the ground.  The High Elves of Felwithe could either blow the entrance or fight it out....eventually losing.  And lastly the Dwarves could also blow the pass or fight.  If they fought they would eventually get pushed back into Kaladim or on a boat off to Velious.<br>
<br>
One big question would be the Dark Elves.  I dont think they would be wiped out, because they have a wide scope of classes and Neriak is a quite formidable fortress, but come to think about it....they just might be able to wipe out the humans.  Think about it....The Freeport human would be attacked by the DE from the West, and the Ogres and trolls from the South which would mean Freeport is gone.  The DE would make a truce with the Ogres and Trolls to leave them be (who really wants to live in a swamp anyway) and would turn their attention to Qeynos.  <br>
<br>
Qeynos in the meantime has been attack by the Barbarians and Half Elves.  When the DEs show up the Barbarians and HE pull back to their homelands and blow the entrances.  being battered and beaten, the Qeynos Guard falls to the DEs in mere hours.<br>
<br>
Just my vision...<br>
