<br>
Odus could not attack except by sea. Not sure anymore but I think the boat from Qeynos has the flag of that city on it. <br>
<br>
The Bertox worshipers would be a problem but not enough to alter the outcome.<br>
<br>
After all Antonica is named after the rulers of Qeynos.<br>
<br>
When it comes down to it, there are not enough gnomes to make much of an impact. Iksar would be bled white invading Antonica.<br>
<br>
I agree with one of the previous posters, Freeport would fall to a combined attack from the Teir Dal, the Ogres and the Trolls who would ally. They would Drive the surviving humans to Highpass where they would stop the advance. Hard to lay seige when Kithcor turns bad at night.<br>
<br>
The Teir Dal army with its allies would then leave a force in the West Commons to keep the humans bottled up and turn their attention to their ancestral enemies. They would take the boats to Faydwer and get involved in a long and protracted war there. The ogers were driven off the continent by the Dwarves and they would basically destroy each other, neither race has the numbers to make much of a difference alone. The gnomes would support the Light Elves and be enough to defeat the Teir Dal, unless Mistmoore came in on the Teir Dal side, if that was the case Faydwer falls to the Teir Dal who leave southern Antonica to the surviving Trolls and Ogers who lack the organization and numbers to expand their territory much further.<br>
<br>
Qeynos captures Whisp Isle and holds it against any agression from Odus, but it never comes since the two cites there destroy each other in a magical blast.<br>
<br>
Cats remain supreme on Luclin and the Iks on Kunark, the Lightbringer fortress of Fironia Vie after a very long seige remains unconquered. I hate those flying critters and it is a pretty well defended area. Only challenge would be from a Teir Dal attack by sea after the fall of Faydwer. But I see the survivors of the Teir Dal victory in Faydwer fleeing to FV or possibly Velious where we get the Ice Elves and the Dwarves moving into Thurgadin. The gnomes seeing the writing on the wall make a seperate peace with the Teir Dal and retain akanon. Overthere falls to Iksar assault, but it is more costly than expected. Iksar fleet lands in Antonica after theTeir Dal take Faydwer, Long war but Iksar capture Freeport ruins, Grobb and Oggok with the assistance of Cazic Thule. They also capture the Commons East and West but cannot enter Nektulos forest and leave that city of the Teir Dal alone. (Keep in mind that the Teir Dal also hold, Befallen and Najena, and Mistmoore soon after the start of the war)<br>
<br>
An assault on Highpass also fails and resistance from the surviving Ogres and Trolls in the Rathe Mountains prevents any further invasion.<br>
<br>
An Iksar assault on Faydwer is also defeated by the Teir Dal.<br>
