<br>
Someone said earlier that disabling the spires meant that no one could get to Luclin. They fail to realize that level 59 Wizards get to transport to Nexus easily, as part of their alternate advancement. I could just imagine it now; groups of Wizards of no one race in particular, sent to lay waste to Shar Vahl, Shadow Haven, and other populated outposts on Luclin with Mana Burn. If enough Wizards were sent, all that would be left of Luclin is a wasteland. But if you're not counting that, then yeah, the Vah Shir could rest easily while the Norrath races were destroying each other.<br>
<br>
Other than that, I think that the races would divide in terms of deity. It would ultimately come down to good (Brell, Tunare, Marr, Quellious, etc.) versus evil (Innoruuk, Cazic-Thule, Bert, etc.), with neutral (the Tribunal, Solusek Ro, Veeshan, etc.) characters sticking amongst themselves or assisting either side. I would say that the goodly races would end up winning, since there seems to be more of them than evils. If we were including NPC races (such as the Orcs, Frogloks, and so on), they'd probably represent their own respective empires, and not join any one side.<br>
<br>
I don't see a Paladin of Tunare cutting down a Paladin of Mithaniel Marr for no reason except that it's an all-out war. There'd definitely be factions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 563<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/27/02 1:05:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2427.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not quite</span><hr size=1> Iksar would not join up with &quot;evils&quot;...they would remain seperate unless their god came down and gave them a direct order to join up with those they would normally despise. Iksar would represent their own Empire and would likely not join any side if such a thing were to occur, although if for some reason they did, I see them being more likely to temporarily join up with the goods. (Which is what happend during the PvP RPing events on this server, heheh.)<br>
